display_name: Body mass index (BMI)
description: Harmonized by the NSRR team to align with TOPMed and BioDataCatalyst standards. Source: :bmi: at Visit 3

display_name: Diastolic blood pressure
description:
Average resting diastolic blood pressure of six measurements (three measurements in the evening and three in the morning) collected from the upper arm in a single day. In cases where either of the measurements was missing, the average was calculated discarding the missing value.

Harmonized by the NSRR team to align with TOPMed and BioDataCatalyst standards. Source: :bpdias: at Visit 3

display_name: Systolic blood pressure
description:
Average resting systolic blood pressure of six measurements (three measurements in the evening and three in the morning) collected from the upper arm in a single day. In cases where either of the measurements was missing, the average was calculated discarding the missing value.

Harmonized by the NSRR team to align with TOPMed and BioDataCatalyst standards. Source: :bpsys: at Visit 3

display_name: Apnea-Hypopnea Index : (All apneas + hypopneas with >=30% nasal cannula [or alternative sensor] reduction and >= 3% oxygen desaturation or with arousal) / hour of sleep
description:
Harmonized by the NSRR team.

The definition for hypopneas is consistent with the following clinical guidelines: (1) American Academy of Sleep Medicine (AASM) 2007 Manual (2012 update) (recommended). [Berry RB et al. 2012 (PubMed ID:23066376)] (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23066376), and (2) American Academy of Sleep Medicine (AASM) 2015 (recommended) [Berry RB et al. The AASM Manual for the Scoring of Sleep and Associated Events: Rules, Terminology and Technical Specifications, Version 2.2. American Academy of Sleep Medicine, Darien, IL, 2015.]

Refer to the source for detailed definition for respiratory events: :ahi_a0h3a: at Visit 3

display_name: Apnea-Hypopnea Index : (All apneas + hypopneas with >= 3% oxygen desaturation) / hour of sleep
description: Harmonized by the NSRR team. Refer to the source for detailed definition for respiratory events: :ahi_a0h3: at Visit 3

display_name: Apnea-Hypopnea Index : (All apneas + hypopneas with >= 4% oxygen desaturation or with arousal) / hour of sleep
description: Harmonized by the NSRR team. Refer to the source for detailed definition for respiratory events: :ahi_a0h4a: at Visit 3

display_name: Apnea-Hypopnea Index : (All apneas + hypopneas with >=30% nasal cannula [or alternative sensor] reduction with >= 4% oxygen desaturation) / hour of sleep
description:
Harmonized by the NSRR team.

The definition of hypopnea events is consistent with the following clinical guidelines: (1) AASM 2012 update (alternative) [Berry RB et al. 2012 (PubMed ID:23066376)](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23066376), and (2) AASM 2015 (acceptable) [Berry RB et al. The AASM Manual for the Scoring of Sleep and Associated Events: Rules, Terminology and Technical Specifications, Version 2.2. American Academy of Sleep Medicine, Darien, IL, 2015.].

Refer to the source for detailed definition for respiratory events: :ahi_a0h4: at Visit 3

display_name: Arousal Index: Number of arousals per hour of sleep from polysomnography
description: Harmonized by the NSRR team. Source: :ai_all: at Visit 3

display_name: Study scored sleep/wake rather than with full sleep staging if there is not sufficient quality on EEG lead. Studies scored as sleep wake have all sleep stages scored using a default of Stage 2 and no arousals are scored.
description: Harmonized by the NSRR team. Source: :slewake: at Visit 3

display_name: Total Sleep Duration: the interval between sleep onset and sleep offset while the participant is asleep from polysomnography
description:
Conventionally, this would be called total sleep time (TST) (i.e. total time spent in stage 1 or greater).

Harmonized by the NSRR team. Source: :slpprdp: at Visit 3

Apnea-Hypopnea Index: (All apneas with no oxygen desaturation threshold used and with or without arousal + hypopneas with > 30% flow reduction and with >= 3% oxygen desaturation and with or without arousal) / hour of sleep from type I polysomnography
description: Calculated - Summary metric of sleep disordered breathing events.
calculation: 60 * (hrembp3 + hrop3 + hnrbp3 + hnrop3 + carbp + carop + canbp + canop + oarbp + oarop + oanbp + oanop) / slpprdp

display_name: Apnea-Hypopnea Index: (All apneas with no oxygen desaturation threshold used and with or without arousal + hypopneas with > 30% flow reduction and with >= 3% oxygen desaturation or with arousal) / hour of sleep from type I polysomnography
description:
Calculated - Summary metric of sleep disordered breathing events. The definition for hypopneas is consistent with the following clinical guidelines: (1) American Academy of Sleep Medicine (AASM) 2007 Manual (2012 update) (recommended). [Berry RB et al. 2012 (PubMed ID:23066376)](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23066376), and (2) American Academy of Sleep Medicine (AASM) 2015 (recommended) [Berry RB et al. The AASM Manual for the Scoring of Sleep and Associated Events: Rules, Terminology and Technical Specifications, Version 2.2. American Academy of Sleep Medicine, Darien, IL, 2015.]

[Search for all AHI variables consistent with the same clinical guidelines within this dataset](https://sleepdata.org/datasets/ccshs/variables?search=aasm15_recommended)
calculation: 60 * (hremba3 + hroa3 + hnrba3 + hnroa3 + carbp + carop + canbp + canop + oarbp + oarop + oanbp + oanop) / slpprdp

display_name: Apnea-Hypopnea Index: (All apneas with no oxygen desaturation threshold used and with or without arousal + hypopneas with > 30% flow reduction and with >= 4% oxygen desaturation and with or without arousal) / hour of sleep from type I polysomnography

display_name: Obstructive Apnea Hypopnea Index: (Obstructive apneas with no oxygen desaturation threshold used and with or without arousal + hypopneas with > 30% flow reduction and >= 3% oxygen desaturation and with or without arousal) / hour of sleep from type I polysomnography
description: Ratio of the count of all obstructive apneas (all desaturations) plus the count of hypopneas associated with at least a >=3% oxygen desaturation to the total sleep time expressed in hours.
calculation: 60*(hrembp3 + hrop3 + hnrbp3 + hnrop3 + oarbp + oarop + oanbp + oanop ) / slpprdp

display_name: Obstructive Apnea Index: (Obstructive apneas with no oxygen desaturation threshold used and with or without arousal) / hour of sleep from type I polysomnography
description: Obstructive Apnea Index at all desaturations  [(Total number of obstructive apneas associated with all desaturations) / (hours of sleep)]

display_name: Arousal Index: Arousals per hour of sleep from type I polysomnography
description: Total number of arousals per hour of sleep. Ratio of count of arousals to total sleep time in hours. [(Total number of arousals) / (hours of sleep)]

display_name: Average oxygen saturation during total sleep duration from type I polysomnography
calculation: ( ( avsao2nh ) * ( timest1p + timest2p + times34p ) + ( avsao2rh ) * ( timeremp ) ) / 100

display_name: Minimum oxygen saturation during total sleep duration from type I polysomnography
description: Lowest oxygen saturation (SaO2)% during sleep

Total number of hypopnea in REM sleep in non-supine position : hypopneas with > 30% flow reduction and with >= 3% oxygen desaturation and with or without arousal from type I polysomnography
Total number of hypopnea in REM sleep in non-supine position : hypopneas with > 30% flow reduction and with >= 4% oxygen desaturation and with or without arousal from type I polysomnography
Total number of obstructive apnea in NREM sleep in supine position: Obstructive apneas with no oxygen desaturation threshold used and with or without arousal from type I polysomnography
Total number of obstructive apnea in NREM sleep in non-supine position: Obstructive apneas with no oxygen desaturation threshold used and with or without arousal from type I polysomnography
Total number of obstructive apnea in REM sleep in supine position: Obstructive apneas with no oxygen desaturation threshold used and with or without arousal from type I polysomnography
Total number of obstructive apnea in REM sleep in non-supine position: Obstructive apneas with no oxygen desaturation threshold used and with or without arousal from type I polysomnography
PSG Quality Assessment: Apnea/Hypopnea scoring problems
description: Due to signal problems, scorer was unable to reliably distinguish between apnea and hypopnea events.  The distinction between apnea and hypopnea was determined to be unreliable.

display_name: PSG Quality Assessment: Arousals unreliable
description: Due to signal problems, scorer was unable to reliably assess arousals.  The scoring of arousals was determined to be unreliable.

display_name: Overall Study Grade
PSG Quality Assessment: Arousals unreliable (REM)
description: Due to signal problems, scorer was unable to reliably assess arousals in stage REM.  The scoring of arousals in stage REM was determined to be unreliable.

display_name: PSG Quality Assessment: REM/NREM Scoring unreliable
description: Scorer noted that there was a problem differentiating REM  and non-REM sleep.

display_name: PSG Quality Assessment: Respiratory scoring problems
description: Due to signal problems, scorer noted that there was a problem scoring respiratory events.

display_name: PSG Quality Assessment: Sleep Wake Scoring
description: Study scored sleep/wake rather than with full sleep staging if there is not sufficient quality on EEG lead. Studies scored as sleep wake have all sleep stages scored using a default of Stage 2 and no arousals are scored.(0=no (full scoring); 1=yes (sleep/wake only))

display_name: PSG Quality Assessment: Stage1/Stage2 Scoring unreliable
description: Scorer noted that there was a problem differentiating stage 1 and stage 2 sleep.

display_name: PSG Quality Assessment: Stage2/Stage3-4 Scoring unreliable
description: Scorer noted that there was a problem differentiating stage 2 and stage 3/4 sleep.

display_name: Percentage duration of sleep with oxygen saturation < 70% from type I polysomnography
description: Ratio of the number of minutes with oxygen saturation (SaO2) under 70% to the total sleep time expressed in hours.

display_name: Percentage duration of sleep with oxygen saturation < 75% from type I polysomnography
description: Ratio of the number of minutes with oxygen saturation (SaO2) under 75% to the total sleep time expressed in hours.

display_name: Percentage duration of sleep with oxygen saturation < 80% from type I polysomnography
description: Ratio of the number of minutes with oxygen saturation (SaO2) under 80% to the total sleep time expressed in hours.

display_name: Percentage duration of sleep with oxygen saturation < 85% from type I polysomnography
description: Ratio of the number of minutes with oxygen saturation (SaO2) under 85% to the total sleep time expressed in hours.

display_name: Percentage duration of sleep with oxygen saturation < 90% from type I polysomnography
description: Ratio of the number of minutes with oxygen saturation (SaO2) under 90% to the total sleep time expressed in hours.

display_name: Percentage duration of sleep with oxygen saturation < 95% from type I polysomnography
description: Ratio of the number of minutes with oxygen saturation (SaO2) under 95% to the total sleep time expressed in hours.

display_name: Apnea-Hypopnea Index: (Apneas with >= 3% oxygen desaturation and with or without arousal + hypopneas with > 30% flow reduction and >= 3% oxygen desaturation and with or without arousal) / hour of sleep from type I polysomnography
description: [(total number of apneas and hypopneas associated with >= 3% oxygen desaturation) / (hours of sleep)]
calculation: 60 * ( hrembp3 + hrop3 + hnrbp3 + hnrop3 + carbp3 + carop3 + canbp3 + canop3 + oarbp3 + oarop3 + oanbp3 + oanop3 ) / slpprdp

display_name: Sleep Efficiency: the ratio of sleep duration (i.e. total sleep time) to in-bed period from type I polysomnography
description: Sleep duration is the interval between sleep onset time and lights on/out-bed time while asleep (i.e. total sleep time, TST), while in-bed period is the interval between lights off/in-bed time and lights on/out-bed time (i.e. time in bed, TIB). [100*(total sleep time) / (total time in bed)]

display_name: Total Sleep Duration: the interval between sleep onset time and lights on/out-bed time while the participant is asleep from type I polysomnography
description:
Conventionally, this would be called total sleep time (TST) (i.e. total time spent in stage 1 or greater).

Total time from lights out to lights on that is scored as sleep (rounded to nearest minute)

display_name: Total Sleep Duration (REM): the interval between sleep onset time and lights on/out-bed time while the participant is in REM sleep from type I polysomnography
description: Total time scored as rapid eye movement sleep (REM) rounded to nearest minute

display_name: Percentage of REM sleep among total sleep duration from type I polysomnography
description:
Conventionally, total sleep duration would be called total sleep time (TST).

[100*(number of minutes scored as REM) / (total sleep time)] * 100

display_name: Percentage duration of sleep in stage 3/4 sleep from type I polysomnography
description:
Conventionally, total sleep duration would be called total sleep time (TST).

[100*(number of minutes scored as stage 3-4 sleep)/(total sleep time)]

display_name: Total duration of sleep in stage 1 sleep from type I polysomnography
description: Total time scored as stage 1 sleep rounded to nearest minute

display_name: Percentage of stage 1 sleep among total sleep duration from type I polysomnography
description:
Conventionally, total sleep duration would be called total sleep time (TST).

[100*(number of minutes scored as stage 1 sleep)/(total sleep time)]

display_name: Total duration of sleep in stage 2 sleep from type I polysomnography
description: Total time scored as stage 2 sleep rounded to nearest minute

display_name: Percentage of stage 2 sleep among total sleep duration from type I polysomnography
description:
Conventionally, total sleep duration would be called total sleep time (TST).

[100*(number of minutes scored as stage 2 sleep)/(total sleep time)]

display_name: Total duration of sleep in stage 3/4 sleep from type I polysomnography
description: Total time scored as stage 3/4 sleep rounded to nearest minute

Self-reported daily nap time in minutes (all days)
description: Calculated as a weighted average of self-reported daily nap time from weekdays and from weekends (ynaptime_s = 5/7 * ywd_napdur  + 2/7*ywe_napdur)

display_name: Self-reported sleep latency
description: Calculated from self report of hours and minutes it takes to fall asleep (ysleeplatency = (yflashr * 60) + yflasmn)

display_name: Self-reported sleep time across all days
description: Calculated as a weighted average of self-reported sleep time from weekdays and from weekends (ysleeptime_hr  = 5/7 *wd_slpdur_hr  + 2/7*we_slpdur_hr)

display_name: Sleep time from self-reported bed and wake times in minutes (all days)
description: Calculated as a weighted average of self-reported sleep time from weekdays and from weekends (ysleeptime_min = 5/7 * wd_slpdur  + 2/7*we_slpdur )

display_name: Sleep time from self-reported usual sleep time (all days)
description: Calculated as a weighted average of self-reported usual sleep time from weekdays and from weekends (ysleeptime_s = 5/7 * ywd_slpdur  + 2/7*ywe_slpdur )

display_name: Self-reported daily nap time in minutes (Weekday)
description: Calculated from self report of hours and minutes spent napping on average on weekdays (ywd_napdur = (ywdnphr * 60) + ywdnpmn)

display_name: Sleep time from self-reported usual sleep time (Weekday)
description: Calculated from self report of hours and minutes spent asleep (ywd_slpdur = (ywdslhr * 60) + ywdslmn)

display_name: Self-reported daily nap time in minutes (Weekend)

display_name: Sleep time from self-reported usual sleep time (Weekend)
